WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.400
Hey, don't you think the most important thing to cooperate with AI is to make the order clear?
嘿，你不認為與 AI 合作最重要的是把要求講清楚嗎？

2
00:00:06.400 --> 00:00:09.600
But to be honest, this is actually only half right.
但說實話，這其實只說對了一半。

3
00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:13.680
The real challenge or the real headache is
真正的挑戰或真正的頭痛問題是

4
00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:16.640
when AI responds to you, how do you know
當 AI 回應你時，你怎麼知道

5
00:00:16.640 --> 00:00:22.320
whether the answer it gives you is a divine assist or a super big trouble?
它給你的答案是神助攻還是超大麻煩？

6
00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:24.400
That's right, this is what we're going to talk about today.
沒錯，這就是我們今天要談的。

7
00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:27.440
You know, AI is really strong, there's nothing to say about this.
你知道，AI 真的很強，這點沒什麼好說的。

8
00:00:27.440 --> 00:00:29.040
But it has a wonderful feature.
但它有一個妙不可言的特點。

9
00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:34.640
When it makes a mistake, it's so confident that it's even more secure than you and me.
當它犯錯時，它自信滿滿，甚至比你我還要保險。

10
00:00:34.640 --> 00:00:35.680
So here's the question.
所以問題來了。

11
00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:38.960
How are we going to tell if AI is really right?
我們怎麼判斷 AI 是否真的正確？

12
00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:42.800
Or is it just a serious mess?
或者它只是一場天大的混亂？

13
00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:45.680
Okay, so how do we solve this trust problem?
好的，那我們怎樣解決這個信任問題呢？

14
00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:50.400
In fact, the key is to train a super important core skill.
實際上，關鍵是要訓練一項超級重要的核心技能。

15
00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:54.640
You can imagine it as a safety net.
你可以把它想象成一個安全網。

16
00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:57.840
With it, we can really exert the power of AI,
有了它，我們才能真正發揮 AI 的力量，

17
00:00:57.840 --> 00:01:00.560
instead of being led by it.
而不是被它牽著鼻子走。

18
00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:02.880
So you see, the key point is out.
所以你看，關鍵點就出來了。

19
00:01:02.880 --> 00:01:05.760
The point is not just that you will give orders.
重點不只是你會下命令。

20
00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:10.320
More importantly, it's actually how we judge what AI gives us.
更重要的是，我們其實是如何判斷 AI 給我們的東西。

21
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:14.800
This judgment is the core that really decides whether we cooperate or not.
這種判斷是真正決定我們是否合作的核心。

22
00:01:14.800 --> 00:01:16.720
Okay, so the so-called judgment,
好的，所以所謂的判斷，

23
00:01:16.720 --> 00:01:20.800
we give it a special noun called AI思辨能力.
我們給它一個特殊的名詞叫 AI 思辨能力。

24
00:01:20.800 --> 00:01:21.920
What the hell is this?
這到底是什麼？

25
00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:23.440
Let's talk about it.
讓我們來談談。

26
00:01:23.440 --> 00:01:27.680
The so-called思辨能力, to be honest, is a kind of assessment ability.
所謂的思辨能力，說實話，是一種評估能力。

27
00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:28.560
What is it?
它是什麼？

28
00:01:28.560 --> 00:01:31.760
It's the process that AI produces for you.
它是 AI 為你生成的過程。

29
00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:34.240
It's even the behavior of interacting with you.
甚至是它與你互動的行為。

30
00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:36.160
I think there's a metaphor that's super close.
我認為有一個比喻超級恰當。

31
00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:39.920
Just imagine it as your own AI control system.
就把它想象成你自己的 AI 控制系統。

32
00:01:39.920 --> 00:01:40.880
Yes, it's a control system.
沒錯，它是一個控制系統。

33
00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:46.160
It's used to ensure that every step AI takes is on the right track.
它用來確保 AI 採取的每一步都在正軌上。

34
00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:47.920
Okay, we can think of it like this.
好的，我們可以這樣想。

35
00:01:47.920 --> 00:01:51.520
Interacting with AI is basically two things.
與 AI 互動基本上是兩件事。

36
00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:54.080
The first one is called the description ability.
第一個叫做表述能力。

37
00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:55.600
This is to make a request.
這就是提出請求。

38
00:01:55.600 --> 00:01:58.800
It's very intuitive to tell AI what you want.
很直觀地告訴 AI 你想要什麼。

39
00:01:58.800 --> 00:02:00.160
But that's not enough.
但這還不夠。

40
00:02:00.160 --> 00:02:04.000
The second one is what we've been talking about, the思辨能力,
第二個就是我們一直在談的，思辨能力，

41
00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:05.840
which is to make a judgment.
即做出判斷。

42
00:02:05.840 --> 00:02:06.720
Judgment what?
判斷什麼？

43
00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:08.640
Judgment what AI gives you.
判斷 AI 給你的結果。

44
00:02:08.640 --> 00:02:10.480
Is it what you want?
這是否是你想要的？

45
00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:13.440
These two abilities can be said to complement each other.
這兩種能力可以說是相輔相成的。

46
00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:15.040
One can't be less.
缺一不可。

47
00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:17.680
Okay, next, in order to make it easier for everyone to get started,
好的，接下來，為了讓大家更容易上手，

48
00:02:17.760 --> 00:02:21.760
we have three specific types of思辨能力.
我們有三種具體的思辨能力。

49
00:02:21.760 --> 00:02:23.120
Once you understand these three types,
一旦你理解了這三種，

50
00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:25.440
you can immediately use them in your work.
你就能立即在工作中運用它們。

51
00:02:25.440 --> 00:02:26.720
It's really super practical.
真的非常實用。

52
00:02:26.720 --> 00:02:29.280
The first one is also the most intuitive and easy to understand.
第一種也是最直觀、最容易理解的。

53
00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:31.280
We call it the result of思辨.
我們稱之為結果思辨。

54
00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:37.040
In other words, it's to judge whether the product that AI finally gives out is good or not.
換句話說，就是判斷 AI 最終給出的產物是否好。

55
00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:40.080
Its accuracy and value are all counted.
它的準確性和價值都要算。

56
00:02:40.080 --> 00:02:43.920
Simply put, it's to directly look at the results and evaluate the product.
簡單來說，就是直接看結果並評估產物。

57
00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:46.720
How do you evaluate the product?
你如何評估這個產物？

58
00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:50.560
You can ask yourself a few questions as a check list.
你可以問自己幾個問題作為檢查清單。

59
00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:52.800
Is this product actually right?
這個產物真的是對的嗎？

60
00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:55.040
Is its structure and logic consistent?
它的結構和邏輯是否前後一致？

61
00:02:55.040 --> 00:02:57.360
Does it meet my initial requirements?
它是否符合我最初的需求？

62
00:02:57.360 --> 00:02:58.800
These are all very important.
這些都非常重要。

63
00:02:58.800 --> 00:03:01.360
But I think the most important question is,
但我認為最重要的問題是，

64
00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.920
did it really solve my problem?
它真的解決了我的問題嗎？

65
00:03:03.920 --> 00:03:05.520
Did it really tie me in?
它真的幫到我了嗎？

66
00:03:05.520 --> 00:03:09.360
Okay, the second type of思辨能力 is called process思辨.
好的，第二種思辨能力叫做過程思辨。

67
00:03:09.360 --> 00:03:11.280
This is more advanced.
這是更高級的。

68
00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:12.800
It not only looks at the results,
它不僅看結果，

69
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:17.040
but also the process and method for AI to get this result.
還要看 AI 得出這個結果的過程和方法。

70
00:03:17.040 --> 00:03:18.240
Why is this important?
為什麼這很重要？

71
00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:20.640
Because if the task is very complicated,
因為如果任務很複雜，

72
00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:22.240
you only look at the final answer.
你只看最終答案。

73
00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:24.240
In fact, you will be confused, right?
實際上你會很困惑，對吧？

74
00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:29.200
So we have to check whether the AI thinking process is reliable or not.
所以我們必須檢查 AI 的思考過程是否可靠。

75
00:03:29.200 --> 00:03:31.200
So in the process of cooperation,
所以在合作的過程中，

76
00:03:31.200 --> 00:03:35.040
we have to open our eyes and pay attention to some red light information.
我們必須睜大眼睛，注意一些紅燈信息。

77
00:03:35.040 --> 00:03:38.560
For example, is the logic of AI strange?
例如，AI 的邏輯是否很奇怪？

78
00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:42.560
Or is it always stuck in a small detail and can't turn over?
或者它總是卡在某個小細節上無法轉身？

79
00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:48.000
What's worse is that sometimes it will also beat the wall and repeat the same argument.
更糟的是，有時它還會原地踏步，重複同樣的論點。

80
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:51.680
These problems are to be caught by process思辨.
這些問題需要通過過程思辨來發現。

81
00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:54.880
Okay, the third type is more detailed.
好的，第三種方式更詳細。

82
00:03:54.880 --> 00:03:56.880
It's called performance思辨.
它叫作績效思辨。

83
00:03:56.880 --> 00:03:58.640
It's not about the production,
它不是關於成果，

84
00:03:58.640 --> 00:03:59.840
it's not about the process,
也不是關於過程，

85
00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:02.560
but the quality of your interaction with AI itself.
而是關於你與 AI 本身互動的品質。

86
00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:03.520
To be honest,
說實話，

87
00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:06.480
how does it feel when you two work together?
你們倆一起工作時感覺如何？

88
00:04:06.480 --> 00:04:07.600
Is it smooth?
流暢嗎？

89
00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:11.200
So what we want to evaluate is the overall feeling of interaction.
所以我們想評估的是互動的整體感受。

90
00:04:11.280 --> 00:04:14.240
Do you think this cooperation is smooth and efficient?
你認為這個合作流暢且高效嗎？

91
00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:17.040
Or do you think it's stuck and nagging?
還是你覺得卡頓又囉嗦？

92
00:04:17.040 --> 00:04:19.840
Is the way AI communicates with you helpful?
AI 與你溝通的方式有幫助嗎？

93
00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:21.840
Do you understand it?
你理解它嗎？

94
00:04:21.840 --> 00:04:22.880
Is it right to change it?
改變它是正確的嗎？

95
00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:24.800
If you make this interaction link smooth,
如果你讓這個互動環節順暢，

96
00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:27.440
your cooperation relationship will get better and better.
你們的合作關係會越來越好。

97
00:04:27.440 --> 00:04:29.600
Okay, so we've finished evaluating,
好的，所以我們完成了評估，

98
00:04:29.600 --> 00:04:33.760
and then the most valuable part of the思辨能力 is here.
那麼思辨能力最有價值的部分就在這裡。

99
00:04:33.760 --> 00:04:35.760
It's not over after evaluation,
評估後並不是結束，

100
00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:38.160
but it's going to drive our next step.
而是要驅動我們的下一步。

101
00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:39.120
In other words,
換句話說，

102
00:04:39.120 --> 00:04:42.080
it's going to turn our judgment into a specific feedback
它要把我們的判斷轉化為具體的反饋

103
00:04:42.080 --> 00:04:44.640
and form an ongoing cycle of progress.
並形成持續進步的循環。

104
00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:48.160
Look, this is a complete co-operation cycle.
看，這是一個完整的合作循環。

105
00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:48.960
It's simple.
很簡單。

106
00:04:48.960 --> 00:04:51.600
First, you use description to give instructions.
首先，你用描述來下達指令。

107
00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:54.480
Second, AI produces the result for you.
其次，AI 為你產生結果。

108
00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:57.840
Third, you use思辨 to evaluate the result.
第三，你用思辨來評估結果。

109
00:04:57.840 --> 00:04:59.200
Finally, fourth,
最後，第四，

110
00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:01.920
you give feedback according to your assessment
你根據你的評估給出反饋

111
00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:04.880
to adjust and optimize your next command.
來調整和優化你的下一個命令。

112
00:05:04.880 --> 00:05:07.040
This circle keeps turning and turning.
這個循環不斷轉動。

113
00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:10.080
The quality of your cooperation will get better and better
你們合作的品質會越來越好

114
00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:11.520
like climbing stairs.
就像爬樓梯一樣。

115
00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:12.960
Okay, we've talked so much.
好的，我們已經談了這麼多。

116
00:05:12.960 --> 00:05:16.480
In fact, everything is back to the most important point.
實際上，一切都回到了最重要的一點。

117
00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:17.280
That is,
那就是，

118
00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:20.480
no matter how strong and powerful AI will become in the future,
無論 AI 未來會變得多麼強大和強力，

119
00:05:20.480 --> 00:05:23.920
our human roles will always be indispensable.
我們人類的角色將永遠不可或缺。

120
00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:24.800
There is a sentence here
這裡有一句話

121
00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:27.120
that I think is really good.
我認為這真的很好。

122
00:05:27.120 --> 00:05:27.920
It says,
它說，

123
00:05:27.920 --> 00:05:29.920
through the cultivation of your思辨能力,
通過培養你的批判性思維能力，

124
00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:32.640
you can ensure that your cooperation with AI
你可以確保你與 AI 的合作

125
00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:36.320
is always led by human judgment.
始終由人類判斷主導。

126
00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:36.960
That's right.
沒錯。

127
00:05:36.960 --> 00:05:38.320
This is what we want.
這正是我們想要的。

128
00:05:38.320 --> 00:05:41.360
This is the real effective way to use AI.
這是使用 AI 的真正有效方式。

129
00:05:41.360 --> 00:05:42.960
So, in the end,
所以，最後，

130
00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:45.280
the purpose of our efficient use of AI
我們有效使用 AI 的目的

131
00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:49.040
is never to replace human thinking.
絕不是要取代人類的思考。

132
00:05:49.040 --> 00:05:50.400
Absolutely not.
絕對不是。

133
00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:52.640
It's to enhance our thinking.
而是增強我們的思考。

134
00:05:52.640 --> 00:05:54.080
And this思辨能力
而這種批判性思維能力

135
00:05:54.080 --> 00:05:57.520
is the key skill
是關鍵技能

136
00:05:57.520 --> 00:05:59.680
that allows us to sit firmly on the driver's seat
讓我們能夠牢牢坐在駕駛座上

137
00:05:59.680 --> 00:06:01.520
in this human-machine cooperation relationship.
在這種人機合作的關係中。

138
00:06:01.520 --> 00:06:02.560
Finally,
最後，

139
00:06:02.560 --> 00:06:04.000
I also want to leave a question for you.
我也想給你留下一個問題。

140
00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:05.680
You can think about it.
你可以思考一下。

141
00:06:05.680 --> 00:06:07.760
When you work with AI,
當你與 AI 合作時，

142
00:06:07.760 --> 00:06:09.760
you are the only one
只有你

143
00:06:09.760 --> 00:06:12.000
who can make that unique judgment.
能做出那個獨特的判斷。

144
00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:13.280
What is it?
它是什麼？

145
00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:14.960
I think the answer to this question
我認為這個問題的答案

146
00:06:14.960 --> 00:06:16.880
may be the most important value
可能是最重要的價值

147
00:06:16.880 --> 00:06:18.800
you have in this age of AI.
你在這個 AI 時代所擁有的。
